Description: Here is a Jimmy Page "Dragon" Telecaster Tribute/Replica Fender Tele. The guitar, originally, was/is a 2015 Fender 1960's Reissue Telecaster. It's ideal for having the exact specs of the Tele Jimmy played. The original body finish is removed and has an authentic looking aged/relic appearance that enhances the overall result. I remove the body finish, aged the back of the body and along the edges. I then hand-paint the decorative, psychedelic Dragon image that is as close to Jimmy's as you'll find. I also seal it with a clear, very thin, nitro lacquer to help protect the artwork. Next, I make and install a custom pickguard made of .005 aluminum sheet and model it to look like his, and then a clear plexi guard over that for protection. I aged the neck all over. I aged all of the hardware. The "V" series neckplate is slightly aged as well. The end result is a flashback to 1968/69! It has a perfect early 1960's relic Tele look with the psychedelic Dragon artwork.! The pickups are Dimarzio True Velvet Tele pickups! The neck has a nice, full C profile! The grain on the body is stunning, much like Jimmy's. It weighs just a hair over 7 lbs.It also includes a brand new vintage style Ace multi-colored embroidered strap that is exactly like Jimmy's from his Yardbirds days, and the Fender G&G Brown tolex deluxe hardshell case it came in originally, just like Jimmy's would have had! It also includes the usable violin bow shown in the photos! Feel free to ask any questions you may have!Shipping in the USA is FREE!I ship international
Title: Fender Telecaster JIMMY PAGE "Dragon" Tribute Relic 60's Reissue Tele w/Case Bow
